Content:

But it has been discussed here a while ago. So i'm not sure if it's worth to ask again in AMA

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> @stock999 instel is off today. As for the KYC, it is enforced for all users during the contribution period.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> It was a must for us to comply with current and possible future laws.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <stock999> @PTYX  Yes, i understand

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <stock999> But probably  others also would be interested in this. Smb thinks that KYC is a right way to legalization, but smb else considers it as problem or an absolute evil. So, may be it would be better to include it in AMA in order to make it clear for all.  Up to you.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> i don't like kyc, but some people need it

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> both realms must exist and inter-operate

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> kyc and non-kyc

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <stock999> @Emmanuel Agree. KYC has a right of existence only for those prefer to pay via bank,  by fiat money. But cryptocurrency must remain anonymous, i.e. no KYC.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> Even buying from bank, kyc shouldn't be considered necessary.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> You don't send a selfie to amazon each time that you buy a book

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> Same should be for BTC or any other coin. It's a number that you are buying, nothing more.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> The sole reason for KYC existence, is governments being afraid of losing power.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> And I couldn't care less about that.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <stock999> The most interesting is that the KYC procedure doesn't resolve any problem. It just creates additional troubles for honest people those want a privacy only.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <stock999> But it doesn't work against scammers. Everyone can hide a real identity easily enough if he wants this.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <stock999> So it is just a useless action, useless expenses for lawyers.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> it is useful for governments - you give up your privacy, you give up your freedom

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> door kickers released if you bad behavior

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> a.k.a. "thinking by your own"

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> All businesses do basic KYC when dealing with financial information though. Banks, lawyers, doctors, and even schools.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> We also can't pretend like we shouldn't worry about money laundering or possibly transacting with unsavory individuals that you wouldn't transact in your daily. I do agree that KYC's get breached all the time and we are using the minimum information that we need to comply. However, I think a better approach is to think of better forms of KYC and anti money laundering that doesn't involve handing your information over to someone forever.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content:
[dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> `All businesses do basic KYC when dealing with financial information though. Banks, lawyers, doctors, and even schools.`
That's what cryptos are intended to fix.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> This society is completely messed up.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> what is kyc?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> basic KYC. it's your name and your address.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> how are you going to go to school? with a hash number?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> i mean sure we could, in a crypto or blockchain utopia

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> but that isn't going to happen.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> and basic AML is making sure you aren't transacting with individuals on certain lists and accounts.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> back in the day, only your name was enough, not even id

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> things worked fine

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> it still works like that in many places

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> There are pros and cons

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> I personally like to know who i'm transacting with.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <Emmanuel> you like, but you don't need to know
